<p>
<seg id=1> Israeli Prime Minister Netanyahu has appointed mid-level hardliner Ariel Sharon as foreign minister. </seg>
<seg id=2> Coincidentally, the appointment was made just before Israeli and Palestinian leaders are to attend a provisional peace agreement conference in the United States for heads of states. </seg>
<seg id=3> In the agreement, Israel will give even more territory in the West Bank to the Palestinians. </seg>
<seg id=4> Sharon's unwavering position is to build settlements in the West Bank for Israelis. He also refuses to compromise on the issue of pulling out troops. </seg>
</p>
